The Adamawa Police Command has arrested four suspects for allegedly kidnapping some people and extorting money from others by threatening to kidnap them. The Command said one of the suspects got N150,000 from his victim after threatening to kidnap him. The Command, in a statement on Wednesday, said it recovered N86,000 cash, three single-barrel guns, threat letters, handsets and SIM cards from the suspects. The statement by Adamawa Police Public Reactions Officer, DSP Suleiman Nguroje, said: “On the 9/4/2021 and 11/4/2021 the Operatives of the Command attached to Gombi Division, received a complaint from two residents of Wuro Garba and Lugga Villages of Hong Local government area that they received separate letters threatening them to pay a million naira each or risk being kidnapped.” He added investigation led to the arrest of Adoneja Dauda, 30 years and resident of Hubbare Village, Maiha Local Government area as a prime suspect that sent threatening letters to extort innocent people. Nguroje added prior to his arrest Dauda extorted N150,000 from one Alhaji Dauda Hassan, a resident of Barkaji Village, Hong Local government area with a threat to kidnap him. The Police image maker also disclosed that the Adamawa Police Command apprehended three other people, namely Miss Daisy, 26 years, Manu Hussaini, 25 and Hamadu Bello, 22, all residents of Garwayel Village, Hong, Hong Local government area over alleged kidnapping. He said: “The suspects sometime in March 2021 kidnapped Alhaji Yahaya BUBA, Alhaji Sule and Alhaji Muhammed Bello, all of Konto Village, Gombi local government area.”